The City Engineer to: i. prepare an Inventory Report for the properties being turned over, ii. provide copies of the Inventory Report to the CGSO and CAO, and iii. include the cost of the assets, if available from the contractor, or the fair value in the Inventory Report;
The CGSO to: i. issue the corresponding ICS or PAR to the end-user upon receipt of the Inventory Report, and ii. prepare and issue the Property Clearance Certificate to the contractor
